1. The goal is to use classes to reuse code.
2. Inside of class methods 'this' refers to class instance.
3. In es6 we not only have access to the class syntax we also have access to function defaults.
4. template strings - es6 feature (` `)
5. Unlike constructor (for unique features) which has a specific name and gets implicitly called
   when we make a new instance , the method (for common features) is going to have a name we pick.